      "role": "user",
      "content": "the way u phrased that \"to create more personalized experiences\" sounds like a corporate way of saying they're basically running experiments on us. if they have the tech to do it, why wouldn't they be using it to track how people react to things in real time? it feels way too specific to be just a coincidence every time my house \"adjusts\" while im upset.",
